<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>give oneself airs • give someone the air</xh5><p> <i>give oneself airs—</i>act conceited or superior: Sally is always <u>giving herself airs</u>. You’d think she had royal blood.</p><p> <i>give someone the air</i>—(coll.) reject or dismiss a person: I couldn’t change her views ... nor could she convert me to hers, even when she threatened to <u>give me the air</u>. <i>Cf.: get the air</i>—be rejected (as a friend or lover): Shirley was afraid she might <u>get the air</u> from her boyfriend if she went out with other boys.</p><p> <i>See also: take air / take the air.</i></p> </entry>
